The paper introduces a new deep learning architecture, NAIS-Net, which is designed to be stable and adaptive to pattern-dependent processing depth. The paper focuses on the mathematical properties of the architecture, including the use of non-autonomous differential equations and the global asymptotic stability of the network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the implementation of the architecture for both fully-connected and convolutional layers, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
